[1] Cholera - Myanmar (Mon)
Date: Thu, 28 Apr 2005
From: Shirley Bannatyne <shirley.bannatyne@masta.org>
Source: Democratic Voice of Burma and MASTA [edited]
<http://english.dvb.no/news.php?id=4601>

4 dead in cholera outbreak at Burma 3-Pagoda
--------------------------------------------
4 villagers died as the result of a cholera outbreak at 3 Pagoda Township,
Mon State in southern Burma which started on 27 Apr 2005.
"The outbreak is affecting Kyunchaung, Kyeinchaung and Khepun Villages in
the northwest of 3 Pagodas," a local resident told DVB. "3 died at
Kyunchaung and 1 at Kyeinchaung."
A doctor who went to the villages told DVB that the outbreak was triggered
by [contaminated] water. At the same time, there has been an outbreak of
foot and mouth disease among the local cattle and some people believe it
could be connected to the cholera outbreak.
--
Shirley Bannatyne
MASTA (Medical Advisory Service for Travellers Abroad)
<shirley.bannatyne@masta.org>
